HEADWORD: Zygosphene
<hw>Zyg"o*sphene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>zygo`n</grk> a yoke + <?/ a wedge.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A
median process on the front part of the neural arch of the vertebrae of
most snakes and some lizards, which fits into a fossa, called the
<xex>zygantrum</xex>, on the back part of the arch in front.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Zygospore</ent>⟦br⟧
